Never mind about the above comments. That does not make sense. I did some test. It looks `partitionMapCond.singalAll()` will clear the signal flag. When the fetcher thread just started, likely it will parking on `partitionMapCond` because leader information is not available yet. That means if the following lines of code are executed after the fetcher thread is interrupted but before the fetcher thread get scheduled to run. Its interrupt flag may be cleared.
initiateShutdown()
inLock(partitionMapLock) {
      partitionMapCond.signalAll()
}
